    (1,1,0,...): őĪ‚āĀ=1, őĪ‚āā=1, all others 0

  Case (1,1,0,...): őĪ‚āĀ=1 means exactly 1 odd cycle.
  őĪ‚āā=1 means 1 pair of vertex-disjoint cycles.
  But a 'pair' requires TWO cycles ‚üĻ őĪ‚āĀ ‚Č• 2. Contradiction.

  ‚ąī Must have őĪ‚āĀ=3, őĪ‚āā=0: exactly 3 odd cycles, no disjoint pair.

STEP 2: Classify the 3 odd cycles
--------------------------------------------------

  Let C‚āĀ,C‚āā,C‚āÉ be the 3 odd cycles (lengths ‚Ąď‚āĀ,‚Ąď‚āā,‚Ąď‚āÉ, all odd ‚Č• 3).
  őĪ‚āā=0 means: every pair shares at least 1 vertex.

