  THE PATTERN (b) TRAP:
  C‚āĀ: 0‚Üí1‚Üí2‚Üí0
  C‚āā: 0‚Üí3‚Üí4‚Üí0
  C‚āÉ: 1‚Üí3‚Üí5‚Üí1

  Consider vertex 2 (in C‚āĀ only).
  The arc (2,3): both vertex 2 (from C‚āĀ) and vertex 3 (from C‚āā,C‚āÉ).
    If 2‚Üí3: 2‚Üí3‚Üí4‚Üí? Need (4,2). If 4‚Üí2: cycle {2,3,4}.
           If 2‚Üí4: cycle {0,2,4}? No: need 0‚Üí2, but 2‚Üí0. Not a cycle.
    If 3‚Üí2: 3‚Üí2‚Üí0‚Üí3. But 0‚Üí3 (from C‚āā). Cycle {0,2,3}!
      Wait: 3‚Üí2, 2‚Üí0, 0‚Üí3: YES this is a 3-cycle {0,2,3}!

  So arc (2,3) is trapped:
    2‚Üí3: may create {2,3,4} (if 4‚Üí2)
    3‚Üí2: always creates {0,2,3} (since 2‚Üí0 from C‚āĀ and 0‚Üí3 from C‚āā)

  If 3‚Üí2 creates a cycle, try 2‚Üí3.
  Then arc (2,4): 2‚Üí3‚Üí4‚Üí? and 4‚Üí0‚Üí? 
